#Lyrics
O Lord, have mercy upon us.  O Christ, have mercy upon us.  O Lord, have mercy upon us. And grant us Thy peace.

O God the Father in heaven, have mercy upon us.  O God the Son, Redeemer of the world, have mercy upon us.  O God the Holy Spirit, have mercy upon us.

O holy, blessed, and glorious Trinity, one God, have mercy upon us.

Remember not, O Lord Christ, our offenses, nor the offenses of our forefathers, nor our resentments against those who have offended us. Spare us, good Lord.

From all blindness of heart; from pride, vainglory, and hypocrisy; from envy, hatred, malice, and all uncharitableness, good Lord, deliver us.

From all inordinate and sinful affections; and from all the deceits of the world, the flesh, and the devil, good Lord, deliver us.

From all false doctrine, heresy, and schism; from hardness of heart, and contempt of Thy Word and Commandments, good Lord, deliver us.

From lightning and tempest; from plague, pestilence, and famine; from war and violence; from sudden and unprovided death, good Lord, deliver us.

From all sedition, privy conspiracy, and rebellion; from all false doctrine and heresy; from hardness of heart, good Lord, deliver us.

By the grace of the Holy Ghost, that we may work those things which are pleasing in Thy sight, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

That it may please Thee to rule and govern Thy holy Church universal in the true knowledge and reverence of Thee, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

That it may please Thee to keep and strengthen all Christian rulers and magistrates, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

That it may please Thee to bless and keep all Thy people, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

That it may please Thee to send forth laborers into Thy harvest, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

That it may please Thee to guide and prosper all those who labor for the Gospel's sake, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

That it may please Thee to open the hearts of those who hear not the Word of God, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

That it may please Thee to give us a true repentance, to forgive us our sins and to strengthen us by Thy Holy Spirit, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

That it may please Thee to preserve all who travel by land or by sea; to protect all sick persons and young children; and to comfort all who are lonely, forsaken, or in distress, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

That it may please Thee to grant us true brotherly love and charitable hearts toward all men, we beseech Thee to hear us, good Lord.

O Lamb of God, that takest away the sins of the world, have mercy upon us.  O Lamb of God, that takest away the sins of the world, have mercy upon us.  O Lamb of God, that takest away the sins of the world, grant us Thy peace.

O Christ, hear us.  O Lord, have mercy upon us. And grant us Thy peace.

